http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Central-team-visits-proposed-IISER-site/article13990238.ece

A central team made a second visit to Berhampur in Odisha on Friday to finalise the proposed site for establishment of permanent campus of Indian Institute of Science Education and Research (IISER).The team almost finalised the site near Laudigaon village on the outskirts of Berhampur. The administration has earmarked around 200 acres of land for the purpose. The high-level team included L. N. Gupta, principal secretary Skill Development & Technical Education of Odisha government, director of IISER Bhopal Vinod Kumar Singh, director of IIT-Bhubaneswar Ratnam V Raja Kumar and chief engineer CPWD Umesh Mishra.Apart from this site, the administration had also proposed another alternative site near Palur hill. But the team did not even visit the site near Palur hill. Later speaking to newsmen, Mr Gupta hinted that permanent campus of IISER is expected to come up near Laudigaon.